President Trump made remarks before heading to North Carolina for a gathering. He mentioned having a great meeting with pharmaceutical companies and expressed optimism about the results. He also noted that the stock market had a record day. When asked about his physical, he said he plans to have it done at Walter Reed within the next 90 days. Regarding the Democratic race, he suggested it was rigged against Bernie Sanders but acknowledged that he had faced a similar situation in the past. He also commented on endorsements from Senator Klobuchar and Buttigieg, implying that there may be quid pro quo involved.